<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id47c8410c-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a" identifier="/us/usc/t26/s9722"><num value="9722">§ 9722.</num><heading> Sham transactions</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">If a principal purpose of any transaction is to evade or avoid liability under this chapter, this chapter shall be applied (and such liability shall be imposed) without regard to such transaction.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id47c8410d-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/102/486/tXIX/s19143/a">Pub. L. 102–486, title XIX, § 19143(a)</ref>, <date date="1992-10-24">Oct. 24, 1992</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/106/3056">106 Stat. 3056</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
